cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.MM 

This paper deals with information theory and cryptography, which are typically covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-categories. The paper also involves communication networks, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper uses simulations to validate the results, which could be considered as a form of multimedia, leading to the possibility of cs.MM (Multimedia).
